==Old English==
===Etymology===
A West Germanic word, of ultimately unknown origin.  Cognate with Middle Dutch ''haghetisse'' (Dutch ''[[heks]]'') and Old High German ''[[hagzissa]]'' (German ''[[Hexe]]'')
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hægtesse/
===Noun===
'''hægtesse''' ''f''

# a [[witch]]
# a [[hag]]

